<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="121" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="121">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="121">
Puparia small in size, elliptical or subelliptical. Margin with one row of teeth. Submarginal area not separated from dorsal disc, with papillae-like markings in some species, dorsum generally with tubercles. Thoracic tracheal folds and pores not discernible; caudal furrow and pore distinct. 
<taxonomicName genus="Vasiform" lsidName="Vasiform orifice" pageId="0" pageNumber="121" rank="species" species="orifice">Vasiform orifice</taxonomicName>
generally notched posteriorly; operculum cordate, nearly filling 
<taxonomicName genus="Vasiform" lsidName="orifice" pageId="0" pageNumber="121" rank="species" species="orifice">orifice</taxonomicName>
; lingual hidden.
</paragraph>
